# Using Git Worktrees
# Source: github.com/obra/superpowers | License: MIT

## When to Use
Use when starting feature work that should be isolated from main.
Triggers on: "start working on X", "new feature branch", "isolate this work",
invoked by brainstorming after design approval. Skip if already in an isolated workspace.

---

## Step 0 — Detect Existing Isolation

Check if you're already in a worktree:
```bash
git rev-parse --git-dir
# Normal repo: .git
# Worktree: ../.git/worktrees/branch-name
```

If already isolated → skip to Step 3 (dependency install).

---

## Step 1 — Create Worktree

**Preferred location:** `.worktrees/` (project-local, already in .gitignore usually)

```bash
# Check if .worktrees/ is gitignored
cat .gitignore | grep worktrees

# Create the worktree
git worktree add .worktrees/feature-name -b feature/feature-name

# Navigate into it
cd .worktrees/feature-name
```

**If .worktrees/ not gitignored, add it:**
```bash
echo ".worktrees/" >> .gitignore
git add .gitignore
git commit -m "chore: gitignore worktrees directory"
```

---

## Step 2 — Safety Verification

```bash
# Confirm worktree location is gitignored
git check-ignore -v .worktrees/feature-name
# Should output: .gitignore:N:.worktrees/

# Confirm branch was created
git branch | grep feature-name
```

---

## Step 3 — Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

---

## Step 4 — Baseline Testing

```bash
npm test
npm run typecheck
```

Both must pass before starting work. If they fail → investigate before adding new code.

---

## Worktree Cleanup

**After merge (Option 1 from finishing-a-development-branch):**
```bash
cd ../..  # Back to main repo root
git worktree remove .worktrees/feature-name
git branch -d feature/feature-name
```

**If discarding work (Option 4):**
```bash
cd ../..
git worktree remove .worktrees/feature-name --force
git branch -D feature/feature-name
```

---

## SOS Pet Conventions

Branch naming:
- `feat/module-name` — new feature
- `fix/bug-description` — bug fix
- `refactor/area` — refactoring

Worktree path: `.worktrees/{branch-slug}/`

Never create worktrees inside another worktree.
